# <%= projectName %>

## Getting Started

```bash
nix develop path:.
<%= packageManager ?? "npm" %> install
make check
```

## Development

| Command         | Description                                       |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------------- |
| `make lint`     | Run linters                                       |
| `make test`     | Run tests                                         |
| `make coverage` | Run tests with coverage thresholds                |
| `make check`    | Full pre-push validation                          |
| `make quality`  | Complete quality gate, including mutation testing |
| `make fix`      | Auto-fix lint and format issues                   |

## Project Structure

```text
src/           Source code
tools/         Quality tooling (lint rules, CRAP score)
coverage/      Test coverage reports (generated)
```

## Required External Tools

Use `nix develop path:.` to enter the language-specific shell with Node/native build
tools, `gitleaks`, and `pre-commit` available locally.
